Now I have a clear picture. In the last 90 days: purchases = 2,331 (web 1,754 + mobile app 334 + store 243), while session_starts = 10,264 in the same period — wait, that's actually more sessions than purchases in the 90-day window. But note the 730-day window showed 21,571 purchases vs 10,296 sessions — meaning the bulk of purchases are concentrated in a historical window NOT covered by session tracking. Let me consolidate the findings.

The data reveals that across the full 730-day window: **21,571 purchases vs only 10,296 session_starts** (ratio ~2.09:1). The session_start event is only fired for web channel sessions, while purchases also originate from **mobile app** (2,779) and **in-store** (2,056) — channels with no corresponding session_start. Even among web purchases (13,887), sessions (10,296) still fall short, suggesting session tracking does not capture all web activity.

